Recipe to create ebs volumes
============================

The recipe takes a the following options:

region
   AWS Region

zone
   The name of an aws zone.

size
   Size in GB

name
   A logical name for the volumes.

Note that a volume is identified by name.

    >>> import zc.awsrecipes
    >>> zc.awsrecipes.EBS({}, 'myvolume', dict(
    ...     region = 'test_region',
    ...     zone = 'us-east-1b',
    ...     size = '50',
    ...     name = 'data',
    ... )).install()
    ()

Now, if we look throug our ebs volumes, we should see 1 with a name of
data:

    >>> import boto.ec2.connection
    >>> conn = boto.ec2.connection.EC2Connection(region='test_region')
    >>> for v in conn.get_all_volumes():
    ...     if v.tags['Name'] == 'data':
    ...         print v.size
    50

If we update, we won't get more volumes:

    >>> zc.awsrecipes.EBS({}, 'myvolume', dict(
    ...     region = 'test_region',
    ...     zone = 'us-east-1b',
    ...     size = '50',
    ...     name = 'data',
    ... )).update()
    ()

    >>> for v in conn.get_all_volumes():
    ...     if v.tags['Name'] == 'data':
    ...         print v.size
    50
